'''Scarlet fever''' is an [[infection|infectious]] [[disease]] that is caused by [[bacteria]]. It is caused by [[exotoxin]] released by [[Streptococcus pyogene]]s. It was once a major cause of death. It is now treated with [[antibiotic]]s. The term ''scarlatina'' can be used to mean scarlet fever.  Scarlatina is lesser form of scarlet fever.

